contentrichtext.text: '''GY''', '''Gy''', or '''gy''' may refer to: ==Measurement== * [[gray (unit)]] (Gy), SI unit of absorbed radiation * giga-year, 1,000,000,000 years (non-SI) * A [[galactic year]], the time it takes for the solar system to orbit the galactic center ==Places== * [[Gy, Switzerland]], a village in the Geneva canton * [[Guyana]] (ISO country code: GY) ** [[.gy]], the country code top level domain (ccTLD) for Guyana * [[GY postcode area]] for Guernsey, Alderney and Sark * 'GY' is a term for [[Grimsby]], United Kingdom in its local dialect * [[Gy, Haute-Saône]], a ''commune'' in the Haute-Saône département of France * [[Great Yarmouth]], United Kingdom ==Transport== * [[Mazda G engine#GY|GY]], a Mazda automotive piston engine * [[Gabon Airlines]] (IATA code: GY) * [[Tri-MG Intra Asia Airlines]]'s IATA code ==People with the surname== *[[Pierre Gy]], French chemist and statistician *Garin de Gy, 14th century Catholic [[Master of the Order of Preachers]] == Other uses == * [[Hungarian gy]], an alphabetic digraph * a digraph in the [[Tibetan Pinyin]] transliteration system * [[GenCorp]] (GY NYSE symbol) * [[Green Youth (disambiguation)]], one of two Green party youth wings * [[Grapevine yellows]], a plant disease * Gy - The on-line charging interface in the [[GPRS Core Network]] {{disambiguation}}
